String greeting = "Hello";

//It start with uppercase "S", so it has some methods:

length()

String txt = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ";
int len = txt.length();
System.out.println("The length of the txt string is: " + len);
// String + int == String + String(int).

toUpperCase() and toLowerCase()

String txt = "Hello World";
System.out.println(txt.toUpperCase());   // Outputs "HELLO WORLD"
System.out.println(txt.toLowerCase());   // Outputs "hello world"

System.out.println(txt.indexOf("Wor"));


String Concatenation
"John" + "Doe"
+ == .concat()

More methods visit Oracle article: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/String.html

